patients with CC genotype. Other clinical and genetic factors may also influence whether a patient of develops Malignant Hyperthermia. Please note: the G allele is thought to confer MH in an autosomal dominant manner and is almost always reported in heterozygotes. The variant is on the diagnostic Malignant Hyperthermia mutation list from the European Malignant Hyperthermia Group (https://www.emhg.org/diagnostic-mutations)."');
